name: OpenAI GPT
description: OpenAI's GPT models are a family of large language models that can generate text, translate languages, write different kinds of creative content, and answer your questions in an informative way.

name: AutoGPT
description: AutoGPT is an experimental open-source application showcasing the capabilities of the GPT-4 language model. This program, driven by GPT-4, chains together LLM 'thoughts' to autonomously achieve whatever goal you set.

name: AgentGPT
description: AgentGPT allows you to configure and deploy autonomous AI agents online. Name your own custom AI and have it accomplish any goal you set. The AI will think of steps to achieve the goal and execute them.

name: LangChain
description: LangChain is a framework for developing applications powered by language models. It enables applications that are data-aware, agentic, and connect with their environment.

name: Haystack
description: Haystack is an open-source framework for building NLP applications. It offers modular components for information retrieval, question answering, and semantic search applications powered by LLMs.

name: MCP Server
description: Model Context Protocol (MCP) server implementation. MCP is a standard protocol for LLM context exchange between agents.

name: Semantic Kernel
description: Microsoft's Semantic Kernel is an open-source SDK that integrates Large Language Models (LLMs) with conventional programming languages.

name: LlamaIndex
description: LlamaIndex (formerly GPT Index) is a data framework for LLM applications to ingest, structure, and access private or domain-specific data.
